# Post-install checklist

This file was placed here by chezmoi. Review and delete when done.

## Remaining manual steps

These are things that cannot be automated:

### 1. Mac App Store sign-in (if not done during setup)
Open the App Store, sign in, then run:
```
chezmoi apply
```
This will install the `mas` apps (Logic Pro, Xcode, Bear, etc.).

### 2. 1Password setup
Open 1Password and sign into your account. Enable the Safari extension from
Preferences → Browser. Consider enabling the SSH agent integration if you use
1Password for SSH keys.

### 3. SSH keys
If you manage SSH keys via 1Password, enable the SSH agent:
  Settings → Developer → Use the SSH agent

If you manage keys manually, generate and add:
```
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "{{ .email }}"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
```
Then add the public key to GitHub:
  https://github.com/settings/keys

### 4. GPG key (for signed commits)
If you sign git commits, import your GPG key:
```
gpg --import ~/path/to/private-key.asc
git config --global user.signingkey <KEY_ID>
git config --global commit.gpgsign true
```

### 5. Alfred
Open Alfred Preferences and point it to your existing Alfred.alfredpreferences
file, or configure from scratch.

### 6. Karabiner-Elements
Open Karabiner-Elements and import your key remapping rules. Configuration
lives in ~/.config/karabiner/ — add this to chezmoi if you want it tracked.

### 7. Restart
A full restart is recommended after the macOS defaults script has run.
All Finder/Dock changes take full effect after a restart.

